# Release changelog (Keep a Changelog)

Use this rule whenever creating or editing a **GitHub release** (`gh release create`, release notes, tag message).

Format: [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/) — newest release first, semantic version tags (`v1.2.0`), present tense (“Add”, not “Added”).

## Title

```
vX.Y.Z — short human summary (≤ ~60 chars)
```

## Required sections (in order)

Use these **emoji headings** for every release. Omit a section only when empty; write `_None in this release._` under **🐛 Bug Fixes** when there are no fixes.

| Heading | Keep a Changelog type | Contents |
|--------|------------------------|----------|
| **Overview** | — | 1–3 sentences: version, theme, who should care |
| **✨ Features** | Added | New user-visible capabilities, schema fields, migrations |
| **🔧 Enhancements** | Changed | Improvements to existing behavior (non-breaking) |
| **🐛 Bug Fixes** | Fixed | Bug fixes |
| **⚠️ Breaking Changes** | Removed / breaking Changed | Major bumps only; migration path |
| **🔒 Security** | Security | CVEs, IAM hardening (rare) |
| **📦 Infrastructure** | Changed (infra) | CDK, custom domain, base-path mappings, `cdk-params` contract, CloudFormation exports |
| **🧪 Testing** | — | New/changed tests, golden updates |
| **📚 Documentation** | — | README, path mappings table, stack parameters |
| **⬆️ Upgrade notes** | — | Numbered deploy / migration / consumer steps |
| **🔗 Full changelog** | — | Compare link + optional commit table |

Link the compare URL: `https://github.com/dbryant4/mealr-api-gateway/compare/vPREV...vNEW`

## Writing rules

- Bullet lists; one change per bullet; lead with the **what**, then brief **why** if non-obvious.
- Reference **`VERSION`**, `cdk-params.json` keys, base paths (`/recipes`, `/ask`, etc.), and downstream stack names when relevant.
- **Upgrade notes** must include deploy order when downstream stacks change (service APIs first, then gateway); call out required `cdk-params.json` edits and **`cloudformation:DescribeStacks`** at synth time.
- Align release version with **`VERSION`** and **`.cursor/rules/semver.mdc`**.
- Do **not** edit past GitHub release bodies unless fixing a typo — add a new patch release instead.

## `gh release create` template

```bash
gh release create vX.Y.Z \
  --title "vX.Y.Z — short summary" \
  --notes "$(cat <<'EOF'
## Overview

…

---

## ✨ Features

- …

## 🔧 Enhancements

- …

## 🐛 Bug Fixes

_None in this release._

## 📦 Infrastructure

- …

## 🧪 Testing

- …

## 📚 Documentation

- …

## ⬆️ Upgrade notes

1. Deploy downstream API stacks (if their `ApiId` output or exports changed).
2. `cdk deploy` in mealr-api-gateway.
3. …

---

## 🔗 Full changelog

**vPREV → vX.Y.Z** ([compare](https://github.com/dbryant4/mealr-api-gateway/compare/vPREV...vX.Y.Z))
EOF
)"
```

## Do not

- Ship a release without a compare link or upgrade notes when deploy/config changes are required.
- Use marketing fluff without concrete bullets.
- Duplicate the entire PR description — release notes are for **operators and API consumers**, not code review.
